author: Katie G. Cotterill
title: Reader’s Lens: Olympic panorama, with duck
text:
Photographer: Kalisa Beyer, Seattle 
Photo taken: Aug. 10, Lake Crescent, Olympic Peninsula 
Photographer’s description: “Capturing the calm, peaceful morning on Lake Crescent before spending three days backpacking in the Olympic Mountains to celebrate my 30th birthday.” 
Katie’s critique: “For me, this photo defines serenity. The exposure it great. The silhouetted duck along with the soft and fading mountainscape keep to the same beautiful gray-blue palette. I might crop up just slightly to get those rocks in the lower-left out of the frame to clean it up. This looks like the perfect way to start your 30s.” Most Read Stories
